ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Find a place to get mental health treatment
Get transportatiion to a mental health care service
Clearly tell the staff what is troubling me
Understand the information given to me by the staff
Be able to follow the treatment recommendations made by the staff
Cope well with the consequences of seeking care (for example, treatments, tests, hospitalizations)
Cope well with my family and friends reactions to me seeking mental health treatment
Cope well with the attitudes that the staff may have towards me
Overcome any embarassment I may have about seeking mental health treatment
SE-KNOW Factor 1; Confidence in Knowledge subscale  score
SE-COPE Factor 2; Confidence in Coping subscale score
SE-Total Raw Score
Study Phase
Notes: 1=Phase 1: Treatment as Usual(TAU); 2=Phase 2: Screening Only; 3=Phase 3: Intervention; 4=Focus Groups; 5=Open Trial; 6=Randomized Trial; -888=Not Applicable; -999=Missing;

ElementDescription: Treatment condition
Timepoint/visit label
